Environment
- conda create -n music python=3.10
- conda activate music
- pip install -r requirements.txt

Usage
- Make new data, save the data, train model for 360 epochs, name the output files, generate music and save the midi file
  $ python pipeline.py -m 'bach/*' -n bach -s -t

Arguments
    '-m',  '--Music',     input .mid foldernames or regex pattern
    '-t',  '--Train',     Whether to train a model
    '-n',  '--Name',      Naming for saved/cached files (data, figures, models, generated music)
    '-e',  '--Epochs',    Number of training epochs
    '-s',  '--SaveData',  Whether to save preprocessed data
    '-l',  '--LoadData',  Whether to load preprocessed data
    '-u',  '--Use',       Whether to use load a model's saved weights
    '-b',  '--BatchSize', Model training batchsize
    '-v',  '--Verbose',   Model training console log
    '-nn', '--NumNotes',  Number of notes to generate
    '-lb', '--Lookback',  Lookback of model architecture
    '-cpu','--cpu',       Whether to use CPU for training (i.e. not use GPU)